Subject: RE: [VB] pulley ratio

  It seems that mosy people who run the 356 pully also run at 3000-3200
rpms, which in turn would probally be the same as 3800 with the stock pully.

  I did a simple test with fan speed in my bus. At 3800 rpm's it was blowing
air out of the defroster vent like no tomorrow, as I increased my rpm's the
air started to slow down. At 5000 rpms it was almost half of what I had at
3800

ronnie

