Hey Ronnie,
Do you or anybody else who has maybe done the math, know the % change in
fan speed using the 356 pulley?  I was thinking since I was now running a
3.88 with late reduction boxes, 215/15 rear tires that maybe that would
take up the slack and I would turn slow enough.  I do cruise at 3700
though.  I have a 914 engine in it now but am running a standard T1
fan/alternator.  I know you aren't too partial to using 356 pulleys, but
if you gear way up the engine is making more heat along with pushing less
air from dropped rpms.  I ran the thing up Tijeras canyon 80mph the other
day and it probably got 240-250.  Maybe this isn't that bad for T4 engines
though.
John


